Evaluate \begin{align*}
\left(c^c-c(c-1)^c\right)^c
\end{align*} when $c=3$.

code:
To evaluate the given expression when $c=3$, we will substitute $c=3$ into the expression and simplify step by step.
Step 1: Substitute $c=3$ into the expression.
\begin{align*}
\left(c^c-c(c-1)^c\right)^c
\end{align*}
becomes
\begin{align*}
\left(3^3-3(3-1)^3\right)^3
\end{align*}
Step 2: Evaluate the expressions inside the parentheses.
\begin{align*}
\left(3^3-3(3-1)^3\right)^3
\end{align*}
becomes
\begin{align*}
\left(27-3(2)^3\right)^3
\end{align*}
Step 3: Evaluate the expression $2^3$.
\begin{align*}
\left(27-3(2)^3\right)^3
\end{align*}
becomes
\begin{align*}
\left(27-3(8)\right)^3
\end{align*}
Step 4: Multiply $3$ and $8$.
\begin{align*}
\left(27-3(8)\right)^3
\end{align*}
becomes
\begin{align*}
\left(27-24\right)^3
\end{align*}
Step 5: Subtract $24$ from $27$.
\begin{align*}
\left(27-24\right)^3
\end{align*}
becomes
\begin{align*}
(3)^3
\end{align*}
Step 6: Evaluate the expression $(3)^3$.
\begin{align*}
(3)^3
\end{align*}
becomes
\begin{align*}
27
\end{align*}
Now that we have simplified the expression, we can conclude that the final answer is:
\boxed{27}
