2. The last digit (ones place) needs to be even, so it can be 2 or 4. Since each digit can be used more than once, there are 2 options for the ones place.
3. The middle digit (tens place) can be any of the 5 digits (1, 2, 3, 4, 5) since repetition is allowed. So, there are 5 options for the tens place.
